OL,3,CFire Service employer pleads guilty to
OL,4,CHaut du Mont explosion charges
OL,6,FThe case follows an investigation by
OL,7,Fthe Health and Safety Inspectorate,
OL,8,FJersey's independent health and safety
OL,9,Fregulator, into the actions of the
OL,10,FStates of Jersey Fire and Rescue
OL,11,FService and their emergency services
OL,12,Fcontrol centre on 9 December 2022, on
OL,13,For prior to the explosion at Haut du
OL,14,FMont on 10 December 2022.
OL,16,FThe night before the explosion,
OL,17,Fresidents reported smelling gas to the
OL,18,FFire Service, who attended the block
OL,19,Fof flats, along with gas engineers.
