OL,6,FThe island's Chief Fire Officer, Paul
OL,7,FBrown, said: "We remain deeply
OL,8,Fsaddened by the tragic events of 10
OL,9,FDecember 2022 at Haut du Mont and
OL,10,Fcontinue to fully support the
OL,11,Finvestigations that have taken place.
OL,13,F"We have already made changes to
OL,14,Fstrengthen arrangements and to reduce
OL,15,Frisk. We will not stop learning and
OL,16,Fimplementing improvements from all
OL,17,Fincidents, in Jersey and elsewhere,
OL,18,Fand we will share our learning to help
OL,19,Fothers.
